de.cocolab.reuse
Class DynArrayByte

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--de.cocolab.reuse.DynArrayByte
public class DynArrayByte
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Dynamic flexible arrays of element type byte.

For comfortable programming each DynArray is an object that can receive messages like resize, extend, and shrink. Example: 

      DynArrayByte list = new DynArrayByte(100);
      list.extend(); // doubles the array size
      x = list.get(105);
      list.set(107, x);

For maximum performance you can instead use the static methods resize, extend, and shrink. Example: 

      byte[] list = new byte[100];
      list = DynArrayByte.extend(list);
      x = list[105];
      list[107] = x;

You must remember that resizing the array in this way gives a new object: you must not make copies of the object reference, as they would refer to the old (smaller) array object.

All methods are final to allow optimisation by Java compilers.
